3.2 Model Architectures
Model Input Process. Given that the original data may come in various formats with high dimensions, we first map all modalities to a latent space and undertake a latent diffusion process. Following the process in [20], the RGB image xI is initially processed through a pre-trained, frozen VAE[23] encoder εI to derive the latent representation εI (xI ). This latent representation is then converted into a sequence of tokens tI with embedding size h via tokenizer. Similarly, the robot pose xA is encoded using a Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) [24] into εA(xA) and linearly transformed into tokens tA with the same embedding size h. If available, the depth image is downsampled and tokenized into tE. The natural language instruction is processed through a frozen CLIP encoder [25] to produce the text embedding cl.
