A.3 Real world Experiment Details
Expert data collection. We collected data on 6 categories of tasks, including button press, cableroute, pick and place, and drawer open/close. For the pick task, we include 4 colors of blocks. For the place task, we include 3 colors of plate. We randomly placed 1-5 objects on the table and asked the robot to pick/place certain objects conditioned on instruction. Some samples of expert demonstrations are visualized in Figure 11.
Generalization Test Task Samples. We test the generalization ability of learned policy under numerous unseen objects. The unseen task is much more complicated than expert tasks, as shown in Figure 12. For convenience, videos of PAD can be found at https://sites.google.com/ view/pad-paper.
